		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>pubby</b> [ Sun Apr 23, 2017 10:14 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Lunar Limit (Ludum Dare)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The game I made for this week's Ludum Dare is called <em>Lunar Limit</em>. It's an early 1980s-esque arcade shooter about blasting space ships and dodging bullets. In the game, you're in control of a miniature version of planet earth; &quot;Mini Earth&quot;, and must use your faithful satellite; &quot;The Moon Cannon&quot;, to survive.<br /><br />Controls:<br /><ul><li>DPad - Move Earth</li><li>A/B - Rotate moon</li><li>Select - Use Powerup</li></ul><br />Let me know if you find any serious bugs before I submit it to the Ludum Dare website.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /> <br /><br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/Cs7A9Ol.png" alt="Image" /><img src="http://imgur.com/qdyDYG4l.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Video: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hya0hYITBwQ">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hya0hYITBwQ</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Enjoy!<br /><br />Edit: I've fixed a rarely-occuring crash and have uploaded a second rom.

		
			<br clear="all" /><br />

